    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1908-02-10T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1908-02-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="382"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d382">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 2126/120.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Furniss</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Port au Prince</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-02-10">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 10, 1908</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Our consular agent at Gonaives has telegraphed: “Haitian refugees are out.”</p>
                <p>Investigation shows that they escaped from the consulate at their own risk and
                    peril.</p>
                <pb facs="0535" n="433" xml:id="pg_433"/>
                <p>Consul of the United States at Cape Haitien has reported that he has five Haitian
                    refugees who took no part in the revolution, and will probably be allowed to
                    leave consulate.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Furniss.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
